docs.abstract: One U.S. company is helping Ukraine behind the scenes combat not only attacks from traditional weapons but invisible ones, too.
docs.snippet: One U.S. company is helping Ukraine behind the scenes combat not only attacks from traditional weapons but invisible ones, too.
docs.lead_paragraph: Moderator: Steven Erlanger, Europe-based diplomatic correspondent for The New York Times

headline.main: Rethinking Security When So Many Threats Are Invisible

docs.abstract: The $69 billion video game acquisition is expected to be finalized soon after the sign-off from British regulators.
docs.snippet: The $69 billion video game acquisition is expected to be finalized soon after the sign-off from British regulators.
docs.lead_paragraph: British regulators on Friday gave final approval to Microsoft’s $69 billion acquisition of the video game publisher Activision Blizzard, the last major obstacle for a deal that at one point seemed to be falling apart because of government objections on both sides of the Atlantic.

headline.main: Microsoft Finally Closes In on Activision Deal After Key Approval

docs.abstract: The 3 percent reduction in the company’s global work force follows 716 layoffs in May.
docs.snippet: The 3 percent reduction in the company’s global work force follows 716 layoffs in May.
docs.lead_paragraph: LinkedIn, the professional social networking platform owned by Microsoft, said on Monday that it would cut about 668 jobs, or roughly 3 percent of its work force.

headline.main: LinkedIn Cuts 668 Jobs in Second Layoff Round This Year

docs.abstract: Satya Nadella, the chief executive of Microsoft, is the government’s biggest-name witness in its landmark antitrust case against Google.
docs.snippet: Satya Nadella, the chief executive of Microsoft, is the government’s biggest-name witness in its landmark antitrust case against Google.
docs.lead_paragraph: Satya Nadella, Microsoft’s chief executive, testified on Monday that Google’s power in online search was so ubiquitous that even his company found it difficult to compete on the internet, becoming the government’s highest-profile witness in its landmark antitrust trial against the search giant.

headline.main: Microsoft C.E.O. Testifies That Google’s Power in Search Is Ubiquitous
headline.print_headline: Rival C.E.O. Says Power Of Google Is Ubiquitous

byline.original: By David McCabe and Cecilia Kang
